Dialogue: 10,0:01:34.39,0:01:38.33,Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, they say Miss Lewis \Nis coming this evening.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.33,0:01:40.20,Top,,0,0,0,,Then it won’t be long.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.77,0:01:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Miss Lewis coming in Miss Kennedy’s stead?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:44.94,0:01:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So I heard.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.54,0:01:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What sort of mistress is she?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.74,0:01:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We know nothing of her.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.51,0:01:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When we came to St. Clare's, \Nshe was already ill and on sick leave.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.75,0:01:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The seniors say she is brilliantly original. {unique}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.98,0:01:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In what way?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.32,0:02:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.44,0:02:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.89,0:02:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks has run away!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.06,0:02:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.03,0:02:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your aunt called.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.37,0:02:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?! He’s run off five times already?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.94,0:02:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, I really didn't wish to trouble you.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.65,0:02:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, he was soon found \Nall the previous times.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.12,0:02:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time, Binks simply wouldn't \Ncome back to me no matter how many times I called. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.16,0:02:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{? probably "s[onna]"}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.69,0:02:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering if you could perhaps \Ndo something about it?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.39,0:02:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so sudden, how do you expect me...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.00,0:02:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, \NI have to leave for France shortly.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.92,0:02:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray, do try to help me!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.90,0:02:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But where on earth might my dear Binks be? {?? kanjin = essential; important; crucial; vital; main}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.57,0:02:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I daresay he’ll head your way.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.27,0:02:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely not!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.64,0:02:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He always bolts towards St. Clare's \Nwhen he runs away.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.71,0:03:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll be sure to come there.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.85,0:03:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.49,0:03:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks! Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.27,0:03:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.07,0:03:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen! It’s best we wait here.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.04,0:03:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite so! You can't know \Nfrom which direction he’ll come.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.56,0:03:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, do you think Binks will really return here?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.58,0:03:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he runs, \Nit must take him half a day at least.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.05,0:03:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, when you took Binks away, \Nyou rode your aunt's motor-car, did you not?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.19,0:03:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Could a dog really remember the road like that?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.54,0:03:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There are tales of dogs travelling \Nthousands of miles to their owners, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.56,0:03:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are just tales, aren’t they?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.50,0:03:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are true, I assure you.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.40,0:03:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.37,0:03:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll come back!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.48,0:03:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks will surely return here.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.89,0:04:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... We must get towels ready.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.39,0:04:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll go fetch them.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.52,0:04:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The rain stopped.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.98,0:04:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s supper time already.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.33,0:04:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We must be off.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.60,0:04:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll remain here.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.30,0:04:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So will I.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.57,0:05:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But if too many are absent, \Nthe mistresses will notice and we'll get in a row.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.22,0:05:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the three of us will stay. \NYou girls go.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.27,0:05:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.49,0:05:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.18,0:05:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.50,0:05:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.84,0:05:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A stray, perhaps? \NAlthough he's far too dear for that.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.34,0:05:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And he doesn’t look frightened in the least.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.34,0:05:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s your name, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.95,0:05:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No answer, of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.68,0:05:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, off to home you go.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.62,0:05:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, there’s nothing for you \Nif you come with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.89,0:06:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So do go back, will you?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.60,0:06:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m at my wits’ end...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.37,0:06:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing good in following me, \Neven if you {\i1}are{\i0} a stray.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.04,0:06:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I really can't keep you.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.36,0:06:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oi! See? A candy!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.42,0:06:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.05,0:07:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I heard a noise.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.85,0:07:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.18,0:07:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oi! You mustn’t go that way!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.47,0:07:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so it's just a person. {meaning not dog}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.33,0:07:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.44,0:07:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.35,0:07:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.55,0:07:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.14,0:07:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you're wet through!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.62,0:07:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.29,0:07:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You must've been cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.96,0:07:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How splendid! \NNow then, off we go!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.79,0:07:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.30,0:07:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oi, you! Wait up!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.80,0:07:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't keep dogs in that school!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.34,0:07:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why ever not?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.71,0:07:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Wh–Why not?"
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.67,0:07:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t see why you should be telling us that.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.74,0:07:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite right—who are you, anyway?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.04,0:08:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you be a senior?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.78,0:08:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, actually, I...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.30,0:08:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! You must be a new girl.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.44,0:08:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that explains it!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.69,0:08:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,As for Binks, we’re the ones who keep him, \Nso kindly mind your own business.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.79,0:08:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But St. Clare's has a rule \Nagainst keeping pets, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.31,0:08:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dash! You sound just like a mistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.86,0:08:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re a pupil, \Nyou ought to stand on our side.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.00,0:08:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.97,0:08:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.54,0:08:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just returned!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.16,0:08:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis, you’re looking quite recovered.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.08,0:08:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.51,0:08:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I ought to have been here sooner, \Nbut I missed the bus and had to walk.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.57,0:08:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Golly!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.12,0:08:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,S-So, this is Miss Lewis, then? \NA real mistress?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.54,0:08:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, not a new student. \NSorry to disappoint.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.40,0:08:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Kathleen, about Binks—\NI’ve already heard from the matron.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.64,0:09:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, do let me keep Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.46,0:09:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! That’s the only way.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.96,0:09:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, we’ll speak of that later.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.22,0:09:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, the lot of you must go \Nand have supper.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.98,0:09:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes, supper!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.49,0:09:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m famished. \NCome along, quickly, quickly!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.32,0:09:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.22,0:09:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks, was it?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.24,0:09:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how often I sent him off, \Nhe kept following me.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.04,0:09:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... They say dogs can tell at once \Nif this or that person likes them.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.18,0:09:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that so, Kathleen?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.26,0:09:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, quite so.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.95,0:09:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s nonsense.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:43.05,0:09:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was little, a big dog barked at me, \Nand I’ve never liked them since.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.02,0:09:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, she looks as if she’d agree \Nto overlook us keeping him.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.49,0:09:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What’s the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.23,0:10:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, M-Miss Lewis, \Nif you’d care for an apple, I have one.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.88,0:10:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve never cared for apples.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.34,0:10:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.51,0:10:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I quite see your position.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.41,0:10:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But as long as the rule against pupils \Nkeeping pets on the school premises stands firm...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.39,0:10:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Ma'am!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.52,0:10:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been listening for a while, \Nand I really think you’re being too unreasonable.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.63,0:10:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If something is forbidden, \Nit’s forbidden to the end of time. {lit: no matter if the world turns upside down}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.83,0:10:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.36,0:10:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The rules say so, \Nand they aren't there for decoration.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.20,0:10:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one but Kathleen can keep Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.34,0:10:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! He’ll only run away from anyone else.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.08,0:10:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that sort of sentimental talk won’t do.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.48,0:10:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The point at issue is the school rule.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.23,0:10:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.23,0:10:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s late tonight, so we’ll leave it at that.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.42,0:10:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll decide on the best course \Nin a couple of days.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.92,0:11:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, Binks must stay \Nin the stables as before.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.93,0:11:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear, Kathleen?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.88,0:11:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If only Miss Kennedy were here, \Nshe’d side with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.44,0:11:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.69,0:11:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well, tomorrow we’ll hold a debate \Non rules and regulations,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.88,0:11:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and think the matter \Nthrough carefully, together!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.55,0:11:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.05,0:11:30.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right! We’ll floor Miss Lewis! {argue into silence}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.01,0:11:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,From today on, I shall give you history lessons.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.91,0:11:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But today, instead, \Nwe’ll devote the hour to a debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.02,0:11:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean to drop a lesson? {to smash; to crush - meaning to use the time not as intended}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.35,0:12:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Drop” is not the word. \NIt’s part of our studies too.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.04,0:12:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But what has history to do \Nwith keeping a dog?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.56,0:12:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you speak, give your name.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:12.27,0:12:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.05,0:12:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, so you’re the Head Girl.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.84,0:12:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let me ask—why do we study history?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.07,0:12:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn from the past and apply it to the present.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.76,0:12:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely—to apply it to the present!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.84,0:12:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So that now, and in the future, \Nwe may live better lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.45,0:12:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then to consider the school rules, \Nthat is to say the rules governing our lives, {liberal}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.85,0:12:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is most important when pondering how we shall \Ncomport ourselves now and in the years to come.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.23,0:12:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This, too, makes for a worthy lesson in history.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.80,0:12:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, according to our Byronist creed,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.07,0:12:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the history of the world \Nis nothing but the biographies of great men.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.14,0:12:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, does anyone wish to speak?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.08,0:12:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.98,0:13:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the one who's Pat?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.21,0:13:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.48,0:13:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen has no mother, you know, \Nnor any siblings, and her father lives abroad.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.72,0:13:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To Kathleen, Binks is more than a pet.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.20,0:13:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if we move such sentiments aside... {emotional argument/appeal to emotion}{???? dakara is not "but" so idk what she means}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.46,0:13:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not sentiment!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.23,0:13:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks is like a brother to Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.47,0:13:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We must absolutely first understand \Nhow important that is.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.67,0:13:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if he is like a brother, he should be allowed \Nto live with us here at St. Clare's, is that it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.91,0:13:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.78,0:13:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Pat here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.79,0:13:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said yesterday, \Nno one but Kathleen can keep Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.66,0:13:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no mere sentiment; \Nit is a fact which we must accept.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.49,0:13:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a friend who adores dogs—\Nany dog will take to her.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.67,0:13:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we entrust him to her?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.24,0:13:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.21,0:14:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the aim of education?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.34,0:14:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew! Now you’re aiming high. {lit: came out big}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.28,0:14:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it is not to make machines, \Nbut to make men.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.45,0:14:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A phrase of Jean-Jacques Rousseau, is it not?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.95,0:14:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,See? This is becoming a lesson in history, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.42,0:14:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To make men is to form character.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.49,0:14:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks is necessary \Nto Kathleen’s formation of character.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:23.95,0:14:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gone all in! {??? maybe "she said it!"}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.45,0:14:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been times when I, downcast,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.97,0:14:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,have pondered what school \Nand education truly mean.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.46,0:14:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Sheila.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.41,0:14:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet now! Do not be too smug. {lit: don't think you've won just yet}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.15,0:14:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,School rules are made with the forming \Nof pupils’ characters in mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.56,0:14:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,May I?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.52,0:14:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.69,0:14:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates said:
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.39,0:14:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Even a bad law, being law, \Nmust be obeyed."
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.86,0:14:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So even a bad regulation...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.73,0:14:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.50,0:15:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you arguing for the rule now?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.22,0:15:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not so.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.84,0:15:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Only that such regulations \Nare not easily altered,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.51,0:15:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and unless we recognise that, \Nwe cannot move forward. {??? very complex sentence, kinda confusing: Unless we recognize that school rules are something that cannot be changed, we will not be able to move forward even one step.}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:10.98,0:15:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Janet.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.01,0:15:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How, then, may a rule be changed?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.42,0:15:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,By council—by the governors, the committee, and the mistresses in conference. {riji is director; trustee - it seems she's just using this word as "someone who's in charge"}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.38,0:15:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet so far, no rule has ever been altered.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.66,0:15:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is getting nowhere. {lit: Despair}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.03,0:15:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any who have not yet spoken?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.86,0:15:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You there—will you?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.20,0:15:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison here.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.56,0:15:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should ask the dog what he wishes.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.27,0:15:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.85,0:15:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever Binks would most choose to live with \Nis surely most important—his own feelings matter!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.91,0:15:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A quaint notion, but alas, \Ndogs cannot tell us in words.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.12,0:15:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually... Most importantly, \Nwe have not asked Kathleen her thoughts.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.62,0:15:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Kathleen?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.56,0:15:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak, do say something.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.43,0:16:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Say what you please.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.79,0:16:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be shy!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.36,0:16:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Er...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:03.05,0:16:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.06,0:16:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As for Binks...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.56,0:16:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.57,0:16:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to take him out to relieve himself.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.60,0:16:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Relieve himself?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.51,0:16:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Very well!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:21.35,0:16:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's decided that I may keep you, you'll be able \Nto to speak your mind freely thereafter.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.55,0:16:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What a pity. Has it ended already?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.12,0:16:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis, we have no more classes today.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.93,0:16:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.89,0:16:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s carry on with the debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.00,0:16:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Great idea! Don’t you think, everyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.20,0:16:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.80,0:16:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Right then, seeing as it’s come to this,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.70,0:16:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s thrash it out thoroughly \Nuntil we reach a conclusion!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.34,0:16:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A grand debate!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.94,0:16:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Super-agreed! {dai sansei = great agreement}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.98,0:16:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with, what are rules?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.68,0:17:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They are provisions that must be observed \Nwhen a person undertakes some action.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.54,0:17:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.59,0:17:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Those provisions that must be observed \Nare properly written in the law books.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.54,0:17:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what matters more to you—\Nrules or people?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.78,0:17:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, people, of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.80,0:17:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Rules exist for people.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.07,0:17:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please put Kathleen first. {lit: think of kath before anything else}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.07,0:17:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But the rule that says you mustn’t keep pets at school is not a bad one.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.35,0:17:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For Kathleen as she is now, it is bad!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.82,0:17:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:32.35,0:17:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, rules exist for the sake of people.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.76,0:17:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But not for a single person—\Nrather, for everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.16,0:17:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That, I understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.73,0:17:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, what're you saying?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.03,0:17:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.97,0:17:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn’t acknowledge that!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.13,0:17:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? If we don't recognise what is right as right...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.31,0:17:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true the school rules \Ndon’t contain anything inherently bad.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.44,0:17:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s the trap!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.21,0:17:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The trap!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.70,0:18:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re all things convenient for the school.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.42,0:18:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Not always.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.02,0:18:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, always! For example, \Nwhy shouldn’t we all keep a pet together?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.39,0:18:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the school isn’t a zoo.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.79,0:18:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So what if it did become a bit like a zoo?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.63,0:18:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be wrong! {/a nuisance}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.79,0:18:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn’t!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.56,0:18:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It would!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.83,0:18:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true, among the school rules, there are those \Nmade solely for the school’s convenience.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.24,0:18:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But school rules ought to benefit \Nthe pupils as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.14,0:18:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! School rules aren’t for the school’s sake...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.64,0:18:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re for the pupils!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.25,0:18:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.55,0:18:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Kathleen?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.80,0:18:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks looks thirsty, \Nmay I give him some water?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.76,0:18:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You may, but how do you know he’s thirsty?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.93,0:18:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell, that much at least.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.57,0:18:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Right then, let’s continue this in my room! {lit: let's hold the next one ...}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.22,0:18:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.20,0:19:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This time it seems they're doing it \Nin Miss Lewis’s room.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.87,0:19:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They carried in mountains of biscuits and cakes, \Nand kept at it without a break.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.57,0:19:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, it’s bedtime already.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.99,0:19:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, what a pity.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.72,0:19:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ve not reached a conclusion yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.56,0:19:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everyone sleepy?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.16,0:19:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in the least!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.41,0:19:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{yeah}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.89,0:19:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let’s carry on.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.23,0:19:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if Matron comes on her rounds?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.90,0:19:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll take responsibility.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.20,0:19:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re relying on you. {/please do}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.41,0:19:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks, everyone keeps fighting for you. {/giving it their best}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.38,0:19:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,For people to live together in society, \Nrules are necessary.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.68,0:19:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In wider society those are called laws.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.86,0:19:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And laws must be obeyed.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.05,0:19:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But laws have special provisions.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.96,0:19:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, exceptions.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.59,0:19:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, then this should be \Ntreated as an exception!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.50,0:19:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Exceptions aren’t so easily handed out.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.23,0:20:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We must obtain the governors’ approval. {riji-tachi}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.57,0:20:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! It’s morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.84,0:20:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s continue outside in the fresh air.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.41,0:20:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.18,0:20:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows rules are made to be broken.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.77,0:20:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time it doesn’t look \Nto be so easy for them.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.92,0:20:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s often said there are as many opinions \Nas there are people,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.09,0:20:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and truly every opinion has been aired by now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.26,0:20:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we never reach a conclusion,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.23,0:20:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what matters is hearing out everyone's opinion of this contentious point, and giving it due thought. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.67,0:20:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw Isabel and Pat, two sisters, \Nlock horns in fierce debate,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.74,0:20:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and Kathleen showed us how deeply \Nshe cares about Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.74,0:20:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Above all, it warmed my heart \Nto see everyone’s eyes shining with life.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.60,0:20:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is not the end.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.12,0:20:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll go on discussing the school rules \Nwhenever there’s a chance.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.32,0:20:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But we must come to a conclusion soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.79,0:21:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don’t, Binks will have no place here.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.96,0:21:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, on that matter, \NI shall give the conclusion.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.60,0:21:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.20,0:21:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.57,0:21:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You{\i0} cannot be allowed to keep Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:16.08,0:21:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What, really?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.21,0:21:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what was the point \Nof debating till morning?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.26,0:21:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.93,0:21:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,nowhere in the school rules does it say \Nthat a teacher may not keep a pet.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.76,0:21:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Binks shall be kept by me.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.20,0:21:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you agree, Headmistress?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.23,0:21:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no reason to forbid it, is there?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.33,0:21:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis! {??? assuming sensei}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.98,0:21:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, coming!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.62,0:22:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, thank you \Nfor the biscuits and refreshments.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.02,0:22:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.59,0:22:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The school exists for the sake of the pupils.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.79,0:22:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,For the pupils!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.22,0:23:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, our birthday is coming soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.62,0:23:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, let’s not do anything elaborate,\Njust sit quietly over tea.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.29,0:23:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What? But it’s our birthday!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.46,0:23:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A games tournament, or perhaps \Na fancy-dress party might be fun! {dunno what games this is about since it's obv not VG, maybe tabletops?}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:47.16,0:23:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing too showy.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.68,0:23:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It’ll be fine, as long as we keep it under wraps. {??? lit: if we do it in the way that wouldn't understand - think she means "in secret from mistresses"?}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.63,0:23:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well then. I’ll hold the sort of party I want! \NLet’s keep them separate.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.72,0:23:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I’ll do just as I please as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.06,0:23:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.41,0:23:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Big Birthday Bust-up!" {/quarrel}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.46,0:24:03.89,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 17 \NThe Big Birthday Bust-up! {誕生日に大ゲンカ!}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.71,0:24:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t miss it!
